Changes in this version (V1.6):

- Added the position cursor, and changed some related stuff.
- You can see now how much time is left for thinking.
- A new gag added, which happens when clicking "somewhere" with the mouse
  but it does also occur at random. What it is? It has something to do with
  the little Kick Off players ...
- Another thing changed with a Kick Off player
- Changed the music. The music isn't really a Computer and/or MasterMind think
  music, but I really do not like House and related "music". I actually prefer
  Death metal like Napalm Death, but the new music isn't metal.
- Linked all external files into one MasterMind executable. No longer need for
  octaplayer.library. One advantage is that loading from floppy is faster now.
- Default think time increased to 20 seconds, as 15 seconds was even too short
  for me ...
- If you really cannot find the solution, notice what happens! (Try it)
- Bug fix, only cannot remember what it was. Anyway, it was difficult to find
  the fault. Oh yeah, I remember. Sometimes the "Ok" button didn't work.
  This "sometimes" made it very hard to recreate the situations when "Ok"
  failed to work.
- Hopefully improved the think option. It had a stupid error which I will not
  mention here, I am to embarrassed... and it seems to work alright now!
- Changed the guru message. I got a complaint from a former Commodore Amiga
  Technical Support Engineer about multisync monitor behaviour when using the
  alert message. Hope he is satisfied now!
- Changed the Mastermind Logo.

